      • getRestAdapter

        protected RestAdapter getRestAdapter()
        Returns the current RestAdapter instance. If none exists (first call or API keys changed), builds a new one.

        When building, sets the endpoint, adds the access token to an Authorization HTTP header and sets the log level.

      • getAccessToken

        public java.lang.String getAccessToken()
        Returns the access token.

        It doesn't retrieve a new access token from Orange server but returns the current one you have set via setAccessToken(String) or retrieved via CredentialsService.getAccessToken(java.lang.String).

        To retrieve a new access token from Orange server, use CredentialsService.getAccessToken(java.lang.String).

        Returns:
        the current access token

      • setAccessToken
